    "title": "Vida após a morte",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "vida após a morte",
    "language": "por",
    "content": "<p>Os escritores do Antigo Testamento descrevem o lugar onde as pessoas mortas estão como abaixo da superfície da terra (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:20\">Ezequiel 26.20</a>). Às vezes, a terra os engole vivos (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:31-Num16:33\">Números 16.31–33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:15\">Salmo 55.15</a>). Mas geralmente, &quot;as cordas da morte&quot; os levam para baixo &quot;e os engolem&quot; (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:4-Ps18:5\">Salmo 18.4–5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:30\">Números 16.30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:19\">Jó 24.19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:14\">Salmo 49.14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:14\">Isaías 5.14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:11\">14.11</a>). No Antigo Testamento, a vida após a morte é frequentemente considerada um lugar sombrio e sem esperança de onde não se retorna (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:9\">Jó 7.9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:18\">Isaías 38.18</a>).</p><p>No livro de Jó, as principais imagens do lugar dos mortos incluem:</p><ul><li><p><em>Sheol</em>, que é descrito como escuro e empoeirado (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job11:8\">Jó 11.8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:13\">14.13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job17:13\">17.13</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job17:16\">16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:19\">24.19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job26:6\">26.6</a>);</p></li><li><p>um poço cheio de decomposição (Hebraico <em>shakhat</em>; veja <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:31\">9.31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job17:14\">17.14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:18\">33.18</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:22\">22</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:24\">24</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:28\">28</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:30\">30</a>); e</p></li><li><p>o túmulo (hebraico <em>qeber</em>; veja <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job3:22\">3.22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:26\">5.26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job10:19\">10.19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job17:1\">17.1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:32\">21.32</a>).</p></li></ul><p>O Antigo Testamento, às vezes, sugere o resgate do túmulo (veja <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:6\">1 Samuel 2.6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:10-Ps16:11\">Salmos 16.10–11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps30:3\">30.3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:15\">49.15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:13\">56.13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:24-Ps73:26\">73.24–26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:13\">86.13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:7-Ps139:10\">139.7–10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:19\">Isaías 26.19</a>). Jó espera que <em>Sheol</em> possa aliviar seus problemas (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job3:13-Job3:22\">Jó 3.13–22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:13-Job14:17\">14.13–17</a>). Ele espera que um redentor possa defendê-lo após a morte (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:25-Job19:26\">19.25–26</a>). No entanto, apenas o Novo Testamento promete plenamente a redenção da morte (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:50-1Cor15:58\">1 Coríntios 15.50–58</a>).</p><p><u>Passagens para estudo complementar</u></p><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:6\">1 Samuel 2.6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:11-1Sam28:15\">28.11–15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:20-1Kgs17:22\">1 Reis 17.20–22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:32-2Kgs4:35\">2 Reis 4.32–35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job3:13-Job3:22\">Jó 3.13–22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:9\">7.9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:13-Job14:17\">14.13–17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job17:13-Job17:16\">17.13–16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:25-Job19:27\">19.25–27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps6:5\">Salmos 6.5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:10-Ps16:11\">16.10–11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps17:15\">17.15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:15\">49.15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:13\">86.13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:11\">88.11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:8\">139.8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:7\">141.7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:12\">Provérbios 1.12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:11\">15.11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:19\">Isaías 26.19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:18\">38.18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:20\">Ezequiel 26.20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:31-Matt22:32\">Mateus 22.31–32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:23\">Romanos 8.23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:50-1Cor15:58\">1 Coríntios 15.50–58</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:21\">Filipenses 3.21.</a></p>",
